        "id": "5d4a6f7b-b284-494b-9f47-df336db00436",
        "text": "In PoA-based networks, transactions and blocks are validated by approved accounts, known as validators. Validators run software allowing them to put transactions in blocks. The process is automated and does not require validators to be constantly monitoring their computers. It, however, does require maintaining the computer (the authority node ([[node (networking)]])<ref name=\"enuma-io\"/>) uncompromised. The term was coined by [[Gavin Wood]], co-founder of [[Ethereum]] and Parity Technologies.[https://github.com/ethereum/guide/blob/master/poa.md PoA Private Chains]"
      },
