        "id": "8112d41d-e358-4dfb-8f38-9d0acbb162cb",
        "text": "With PoA individuals earn the right to become validators, so there is an incentive to retain the position that they have gained. By attaching reputation to identity, validators are incentivised to uphold the transaction process, as they do not wish to have their identities attached to a negative reputation. This is considered more robust than PoS, as:"
